# Implementation Plan: Observer (Telemetry) & Messenger (Notifications)

This plan moves the system from "background execution" to "visible action" by establishing a persistent audit trace for agents and a real database-backed notification system.

## Phase 4a: The Observer (Telemetry)

### [NEW] `backend/telemetry_monitor.py`
- **Role**: A standalone script that pulls messages from the `taskninja-events` PubSub topic.
- **Functionality**:
  - Automatically creates a temporary subscription if needed.
  - Formats and prints the "Swarm Trace" (e.g., `master_orchestrator -> scheduler_node -> response_node`).
  - Provides a real-time view of what the agents are "thinking."

## Phase 4b: The Messenger (Notifications)

### [MODIFY] [models.py](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/Hackathons/GenAI_APAC_Hackathon/backend/models.py)
- **[NEW] `Notification` Model**:
  - `notification_id`: UUID (Primary Key)
  - `recipient`: String (Email or User ID)
  - `message`: Text
  - `channel`: String (e.g., "ui_toast", "email")
  - `status`: String (e.g., "unread", "read")
  - `created_at`: DateTime (timezone=True)

### [MODIFY] [tools.py](file:///c:/Users/user/Documents/Hackathons/GenAI_APAC_Hackathon/backend/tools.py)
- **`send_notification_tool`**:
